    {
      "instruction": "<p>Divide the <strong>lean</strong> <strong>beef mince</strong> and shape into 3 <strong>meatballs</strong> per person (clean hands is the best way!)</p><p>Heat a large pot (with a matching lid) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> lean beef meatballs</strong> to the pot and cook for 6-7 min, turning occasionally, until they're browned on all sides</p><p>Once browned, transfer to a plate and wipe the pot and reserve for later (these will finish cooking with the spaghetti later)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1683028138754-x200.jpg",
