          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1683028152884-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>dried oregano</strong> to the pot with your <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong>, <strong>red wine vinegar</strong>,<strong> beef stock mix</strong>, <strong>tomato paste </strong>and<strong> </strong>450ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [650ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[850ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> and stir it all together</p><p>Add <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>chopped basil</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and a very generous crack of <strong>black pepper </strong>and bring to a boil over a high heat and cook for 1 min, stirring until fully combined</p><p>Once boiling, roughly break your <strong>spaghetti </strong>in half, add it to the pot and mix everything together</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1683028159561-x200.jpg",
